.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:39:- [x] T004 Author `lib/resolve.cjs` — the double-gated (`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` AND `servingAuthority: compiled`), fail-safe resolver with a `--hub/--prompt` CLI front-door.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:80:- [x] The compiled-route engine, the double-gated resolver + CLI front-door, and the fenced-CAS serving flip are built and run offline with zero dependencies.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:83:- [x] T015 Wire each hub's live `SKILL.md` routing directive to call the resolver (complete: each of the 7 hubs carries an additive, flag-gated compiled-routing directive).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:3:description: "How the archetype-adaptive compiled-route engine reuses each child's proven engine (evaluateCanary or evaluateRoute), how the double-gated resolver keeps the cutover inert by default, and how the fenced-CAS flip moved all seven hubs legacy→compiled with a byte-exact rollback."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:6:  - "compiled-route resolver flip plan"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:56:- [x] The resolver is double-gated and fail-safe; inert with the flag off; CLI prints the compiled decision or a legacy sentinel.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:59:- [x] Per-hub live-`SKILL.md` routing directive wired to the resolver (complete: each of the 7 hubs carries an additive, flag-gated compiled-routing directive).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:71:Consume-then-serve, gated. A pure engine consumes the compiled contract by reusing the proven canary engine; a resolver decides authority through two independent gates; an operated fenced-CAS flip changes that authority per hub. Authority is data on the activation manifest, never a property of the engine itself — so shipping the engine changes nothing until a hub is both flipped and flagged on.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:75:- **`lib/resolve.cjs`**: serving resolver + CLI. `resolveRoute(hubId, taskText)` returns the compiled decision only when `flagEnabled()` and `servingAuthority(hubId) === 'compiled'`; else null. Reads `010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json`. Fails safe (try/catch → null). CLI: `--hub <id> --prompt <text>`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:94:| P4a activation manifest (`010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json`) | Bound `selectedPolicy`; now `servingAuthority: compiled` (post-flip) | Read by the resolver; CAS target of the flip | Flip asserted compiled `selectedPolicy` and retained a byte-identical serving-prior; all 7 now read `compiled` |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:96:| Runtime flag `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` | Off by default | Read by the resolver | Flag off ⇒ resolver returns null everywhere (inert) |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:97:| Live `SKILL.md` (per hub) | Authoritative serving routing | **Wired — additive, flag-gated compiled-routing directive added** | Each of the 7 hubs' `SKILL.md` shells to the resolver front-door under `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`, self-gating on serving authority; existing prose routing unchanged |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:103:- Inertness: with the flag off, confirm the resolver returns null / a legacy sentinel for a compiled-serving hub.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:125:- [x] Wire each hub's `SKILL.md` routing directive to the resolver and flip all seven hubs `legacy → compiled` (complete, inert behind the default-off flag); post-flip real-model re-verification treated as satisfied by the P4a T9 result plus flag-off inertness.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:152:| P4a activation manifests (per hub) | Internal | Green (bound) | No serving pointer for the resolver or the flip's CAS |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:155:| Real models (LUNA / SOL / MiniMax) | External | Satisfied (P4a T9) | Post-flip re-verification treated as satisfied by the T9 result (0 wrong-hub routes) plus flag-off inertness; did not block the engine/resolver/flip build |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:165:- **Procedure**: Two independent reversals. Fleet-wide — unset `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`, and the resolver returns null everywhere (legacy serves) with no manifest change. Per hub — `flip-serving.cjs --hub <id> --rollback` restores the byte-identical `manifest.serving-prior.json` and advances the fence; confirm `servingAuthority` reverts to `legacy` and `shadowOnly` to `true`. Retain the serving-prior for the full bake window before any cleanup.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:175:Phase 1 (Engine + resolver) ──► Phase 2 (Fenced-CAS flip + rollback) ──► Phase 3 (End-to-end proof on sk-code)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:180:| Setup (engine + resolver) | Rollout children, P4a manifests | Core |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:193:| Setup (engine + resolver) | Med | Reuse the child engine; thin double-gated resolver |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:211:1. Fleet-wide: unset `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` (resolver returns null everywhere; no manifest change).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/plan.md:73:Template-plus-postcondition. Rendering establishes the hub's durable routing instruction; the selected onboarding mode establishes whether a valid manifest exists. The shared P3 predicate, not create-skill, decides whether the resulting hub is compiled-eligible.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/plan.md:40:Add one new parity module at the orchestrator boundary. It hashes the frozen files, asks the shared eligibility/status interface what compiled outcome is expected, obtains legacy and compiled observations, normalizes them, and evaluates both against the existing route gold. The orchestrator adds structured parity results and a distinct gate; the scorer and scenario loader remain unchanged.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/plan.md:53:- [ ] P3 provides shared eligibility and manifest discovery without a local hub list.
