.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/checklist.md:49:- [ ] CHK-011 [P0] Ready mode delegates to shared minter/freshness code and defines no local allowlist.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/implementation-summary.md:36:Lane C will gain a deterministic parity module around the existing scorer. For eligible route-gold scenarios it will preserve the legacy replay, invoke the real public compiled front door with a child-only flag-on environment, normalize both routing results, run the same gold evaluator twice, and require mutual routing equality.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/implementation-summary.md:56:Implementation waits for the stable P0 front-door/status interface and P3 eligibility/discovery interface. After baseline reports and hashes are captured, the new module lands first, then orchestrator/report integration, then the isolated state matrix and non-regression suite. The frozen modules are imported and hashed only.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/implementation-summary.md:70:| Use shared status and eligibility interfaces | Prevents Lane C from inventing a local hub list or alternate drift meaning. |
