.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/implementation-summary.md:3:description: "The P4b runtime engine: an archetype-adaptive compiled-route engine that reuses each rollout child's proven engine (evaluateCanary or evaluateRoute), a double-gated fail-safe resolver + CLI front-door, and a fenced-CAS per-hub serving flip with byte-exact rollback. Proven end-to-end on sk-code, then the cutover executed across all 7 hubs (each SKILL.md wired + re-certified + flipped legacy->compiled), held inert behind the default-off SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING flag; scorer frozen. Advisor-hook machine-enforcement in progress."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/implementation-summary.md:6:  - "compiled-route resolver flip built"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/implementation-summary.md:23:| **Status** | Complete — the P4b runtime engine (archetype-adaptive compiled-route engine + resolver/CLI front-door + per-hub serving flip) is built, proven end-to-end on `sk-code`, and the cutover is executed across all seven hubs: each carries a flag-gated compiled-routing directive in its live `SKILL.md`, was recompiled with archetype-adaptive re-certification, and reads `servingAuthority: compiled`. Each flip is canary-green via the real scorer, route-gold byte-identical, byte-exact-reversible. The runtime path is inert by default (`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` off). Advisor-hook machine-enforcement remains in progress. Commits: engine `d7da0fca43`, sk-code cutover `2fa3357f80`, remaining-6 cutover `337ca43cfa` (pushed on v4). |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/implementation-summary.md:47:| Resolver | `lib/resolve.cjs` | Double-gated (flag + manifest), fail-safe serving resolver + `--hub/--prompt` CLI front-door |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/implementation-summary.md:60:The resolver wraps the engine in two independent gates. `resolveRoute(hubId, taskText)` returns null unless `flagEnabled()` (the process env `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` equals `1`) and `servingAuthority(hubId)` reads `compiled` from `010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json`; on a missing or unparseable manifest, `servingAuthority()` defaults to `legacy`, and any error resolving the compiled route is caught and returns null rather than throwing into a routing hot path. The CLI front-door — `node resolve.cjs --hub <id> --prompt <text>` — prints the compiled decision when authoritative, else a legacy sentinel `{servingAuthority: legacy, hubId}` so the caller keeps the prose smart-router.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/implementation-summary.md:75:| Make the resolver fail safe to legacy | A routing hot path must never throw; any manifest/engine error resolves to null and the caller keeps the prose smart-router. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/implementation-summary.md:109:1. **All seven hubs are wired to the resolver.** Each hub's live `SKILL.md` carries an additive, flag-gated compiled-routing directive that shells to the `--hub/--prompt` front-door and self-gates on serving authority; the directive is inert while `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is off, and existing prose routing is unchanged.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/tasks.md:98:- **Consumed eligibility authority**: `../012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md`
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:64:| Add the directive to every generated parent hub | Legacy and ready hubs should share one durable SKILL.md shape; eligibility is determined by the manifest state. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:67:| Delegate minting and freshness to P3 interfaces | Prevents a second eligibility algorithm or hardcoded hub map inside create-skill. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:92:1. **Ready mode depends on P3 interfaces that do not exist yet.** This packet cannot truthfully select a manifest location or eligibility result before those interfaces stabilize.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/checklists/skill-authoring.md:28:- Use this when promoting a skill from a local draft into the shared OpenCode skill inventory.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/checklists/skill-authoring.md:67:- [ ] Run `python3 .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/verify_alignment_drift.py --root .opencode/skills/sk-code` for the live parent-hub example; use the same script with the actual target skill root when reviewing another skill.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:3:description: "Planned P0-to-P4 delivery sequence for the default-on ruling: establish flag governance and serving observability, enforce drift detection, run a bounded canary, single-source eligibility, then stage the global default-on cutover with a documented kill-switch."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:64:The recommended approach is the ordered P0-to-P4 program already ruled in `decision-record.md`. P0 makes the current flag and fallback state legible, separates drift from breakage in the harness, exposes serving status per hub, and removes or explicitly guards the resolver's dependency on a spec-tree path. P1 through P4 then add drift CI, a one-profile canary, data-driven eligibility, and a hub-by-hub global default change.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:79:- [ ] The P2 canary environment profile and promotion owner are named.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:85:- [ ] Drift is surfaced as drift, resolver breakage is surfaced as breakage, and per-hub authority is inspectable.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:86:- [ ] The two eligibility consumers derive from one manifest-freshness predicate.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:98:Observe, enforce, canary, derive, then cut over. Serving authority remains data-driven and fail-safe: runtime consumption is gated by the environment flag and per-hub eligibility, while a missing or stale manifest follows the legacy path defined by the authoritative contract.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:105:- **Eligibility resolver**: supplies the single derived predicate consumed by both current allowlist sites.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:134:| Runtime resolver/front door | Reads a resolver beneath the spec tree | Promote the resolver to a stable runtime path, or guard and document the coupling if promotion is rejected | Spec-tree move simulation and fail-safe fallback check |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:144:- Locate both current eligibility sets and every caller that assumes their shape.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:146:- Record the resolver's current spec-tree dependency before choosing promotion or an explicit guard.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:157:- [ ] Extend the verify harness so drift-to-legacy is reported as degraded/expected while a broken resolver remains a hard failure.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:159:- [ ] Remediate the runtime-to-spec-tree resolver coupling by promoting the resolver to a stable runtime path; if the operator rejects promotion, add a loud path-integrity guard and document the residual drift source.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:161:- [ ] Rollback: revert the documentation, harness, and resolver-location changes; keep the flag off and restore the prior resolver path if promotion was attempted.
