.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-006.md:7:**Headline finding**: The `code-opencode` surface is governed by **three disconnected drift guards** that each inspect a different layer of the routing contract, with no single end-to-end test covering the chain that the compiled-router + advisor hook claim to enforce. The code-opencode SKILL.md RESOURCE_MAP is locally parseable, the parent `smart-routing.md` flat union is drift-guard-validated by `sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts:119-192`, and the code files pass `verify_alignment_drift.py` — but the **compiled-router output vocabulary (`targetQualifiedIds`) and the surface RESOURCE_MAP vocabulary (`references/...` paths) share no typed-pair contract**, and neither guard covers the compiled→surface agreement that the 015 sk-code-router-alignment spec implicitly assumes.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-006.md:11:1. `verify_alignment_drift.py` does NOT inspect Markdown RESOURCE_MAP. Its SUPPORTED_EXTENSIONS (line 39-51) covers `.ts/.tsx/.mts/.js/.mjs/.cjs/.py/.sh/.rs/.json/.jsonc` only; the alignment-verification-automation.md contract at `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:48-51` explicitly states "The verifier is intentionally lightweight. It does not replace the standards checklists and does not scan markdown prose." [CONFIRMED; refines F-3-8]
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-006.md:13:2. `code-opencode/SKILL.md:45-51` claims "the parent sk-code hub RESOURCE_MAP is the union of this map (re-prefixed with code-opencode/) and the sibling code-webflow map plus the parent-owned universal/shared tier; a drift guard enforces that equality." The cited drift guard is `sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts` (in `system-deep-loop/.../scripts/skill-benchmark/tests/`), NOT `verify_alignment_drift.py`. The latter is the named verifier of the OPENCODE surface in `references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:34`, but it is silent on the parent-child RESOURCE_MAP equality the SKILL.md asserts.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-006.md:31:11. `verify_stack_folders.py` (lines 1-47) validates language folder presence (typescript/javascript/python/shell/rust/config) — disjoint from `verify_alignment_drift.py` (code-file syntax) and disjoint from `sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts` (Markdown RESOURCE_MAP). Three scripts, three coverage bands, no overlap.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-006.md:45:5. **Refactor the alignment-verification contract documentation.** The `references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md` claims authority for `verify_alignment_drift.py` but does not link to the actual parent-child equality guard `sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts`. Add a "Related drift guards" section pointing at the Vitest file path AND the orchestrator hook (`run-skill-benchmark.cjs:219,308`) for Lane C. This was confirmed-asked in F-3-8 but the documentation has not been updated.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-006.md:49:  {"id":"F-6-1","area":"sk-code-align","finding":"The named verifier `verify_alignment_drift.py` is explicitly markdown-blind (support only TS/JS/Python/Shell/Rust/JSON/JSONC; doc line 50-52 says 'does not scan markdown prose'), yet code-opencode/SKILL.md:51 implicitly cites it via 'a drift guard enforces that equality' — the actual guard is `sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts:119-192`, two scripts away and not cross-referenced from the opencode surface.","evidence":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/SKILL.md:51 vs .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/verify_alignment_drift.py:39-51,558 vs .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:48-52","severity":"P0","actionable":"Either rename the inline claim to name `sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts` and add a back-link from alignment-verification-automation.md §5, or extend verify_alignment_drift.py with a markdown RESOURCE_MAP parser gated on a `--check-router` flag (default off) that invokes router-replay.cjs parseRouter on every SKILL.md under `--root`.","novelty":"refines:F-3-8"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-006.md:53:  {"id":"F-6-5","area":"sk-code-align","finding":"Three disjoint drift guards (`verify_alignment_drift.py` code-files, `verify_stack_folders.py` language folders, `sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts` Markdown RESOURCE_MAP) cover code-opencode with zero overlap and no orchestrating contract; a regression in any layer is caught only by the matching guard, and the named 'alignment verifier' in the surface contract documents only the first.","evidence":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/verify_alignment_drift.py:558 vs .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/verify_stack_folders.py:1-47 vs .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/tests/sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts:1-193","severity":"P1","actionable":"Add a single orchestration script at `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/run-all-drift-guards.sh` that invokes all three guards and exits non-zero on any failure; reference it from `SKILL.md:163` (Surface Standards) so the verification gate lists three concrete commands, not just `verify_alignment_drift.py`.","novelty":"refines:F-3-8"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:40:7. P1 — extend the named alignment gate: `verify_alignment_drift.py` currently scans language files and dispatches extension-specific checks (`sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/verify_alignment_drift.py:480-515`), while the router contract it must protect lives in Markdown `RESOURCE_MAP` (`sk-code/code-opencode/SKILL.md:43-51`). It presently cannot prove parent/child router-map equality.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:51:  {"id":"F-3-8","area":"sk-code-align","finding":"The named verify_alignment_drift.py gate checks language files but does not inspect the Markdown RESOURCE_MAP whose parent-child equality it is expected to enforce.","evidence":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/verify_alignment_drift.py:480","severity":"P0","actionable":"Extend the verifier or add a companion check that parses code-opencode RESOURCE_MAP and fails when the sk-code parent projection diverges.","novelty":"new"}
