    13	
    14	# Alignment Verification Automation
    15	
    16	This document describes the repeatable verifier introduced for recurring alignment drift checks.
    17	
    18	## 1. OVERVIEW
    19	
    20	### Purpose
    21	
    22	Defines the operational contract for `verify_alignment_drift.py`, including:
    23	- what rule categories are enforced;
    24	- how severities (`ERROR`/`WARN`) are assigned;
    25	- default vs strict CI failure behavior.
    26	- which standards remain manual checklist gates.
    27	
    28	### When to Use
    29	
    30	Use this reference when tuning recurring checks or interpreting verifier output in automation.
    31	
    32	## 2. SCRIPT
    33	
    34	- Path: `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/verify_alignment_drift.py`
    35	- Purpose: run lightweight, deterministic, behavior-neutral checks across OpenCode system languages.
    36	
    37	## 3. WHAT IT CHECKS
    38	
    39	- **Common (all scanned files)**: UTF-8 readability and LF line endings (flags CRLF).
    40	- **JavaScript (`.js/.cjs`)**: requires `'use strict';` near file top.
    41	- **JavaScript ESM (`.mjs`)**: strict-mode directive is not enforced.
    42	- **TypeScript (`.ts/.tsx/.mts`)**: requires a `MODULE:` header marker near file top, except test files and pattern assets.
    43	- **Python (`.py`)**: requires `#!/usr/bin/env python3` and module docstring near file top.
    44	- **Shell (`.sh`)**: requires `#!/usr/bin/env bash` and `set -euo pipefail` near file top.
    45	- **JSON (`.json`)**: strict parser validation via Python `json` module, with comment-aware fallback for `tsconfig*.json`.
    46	- **JSONC (`.jsonc`)**: comment stripping followed by strict JSON parse.
    47	
    48	### What it does not check
    49	
    50	The verifier is intentionally lightweight. It does not replace the standards
    51	checklists and does not scan markdown prose. These remain manual review gates:
    52	
    53	- exact visual header shape beyond the marker-level checks above;
    54	- naming conventions;
    55	- comment density and WHY-vs-WHAT comment quality;
    56	- KISS/DRY/SOLID judgment;
    57	- JavaScript `module.exports` versus plugin ESM default-export decisions;
    58	- TypeScript package-boundary decisions such as NodeNext ESM versus root
    59	  CommonJS defaults.
    60	
    61	### Severity model
    62	
    63	- **ERROR**: parse/integrity findings (`COMMON-*`, `JSON-*`, `JSONC-*`) in active paths.
    64	- **WARN**: style findings (`JS-*`, `TS-*`, `PY-*`, `SH-*`) by default.
    65	- **Context-aware advisory downgrade**: any finding under archival/contextual paths is downgraded to `WARN`:
    66	  - `z_archive`, `scratch`, `memory`, `research`, `context`, `assets`, `examples`, `fixtures`, and test-heavy paths.
    67	
    68	## 4. USAGE
    69	
    70	```bash
    71	python3 .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/verify_alignment_drift.py --root .opencode
    72	```
    73	
    74	Strict CI mode:
    75	
    76	```bash
    77	python3 .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/verify_alignment_drift.py --root .opencode --fail-on-warn
    78	```
    79	
    80	Notes:
    81	- `--root` is repeatable; when omitted, current directory is scanned.
    82	- Files are deduplicated by realpath when repeated/overlapping roots are provided.
    83	- Output includes both rule id and severity (`[RULE] [ERROR|WARN]`).
    84	- Exit code `0` means no blocking findings (warnings are non-blocking by default).
    85	- Exit code `1` means one or more errors were found, or warnings were found with `--fail-on-warn`.
    86	
    87	---
    88	
    89	## 5. RELATED RESOURCES
    90	
    91	- [code_organization.md](code-organization/overview-and-module-organization.md)
    92	- [universal_patterns.md](universal-patterns/naming-and-commenting.md)
    93	- [hooks.md](./hooks.md)
    45	
    46	```markdown
    47	[ ] File has appropriate header comment identifying the component
    48	    - JavaScript: Box header with 'use strict'
    49	    - TypeScript: Module header block `// ─── MODULE: NAME ───` (no 'use strict'; tsconfig handles it)
    50	    - Python: Shebang + COMPONENT comment block
    51	    - Shell: Shebang + COMPONENT comment block
    52	    - Config: JSONC comment header
    53	```
    54	
    55	**Evidence**: All style guides require headers
    56	
    57	**Verifier boundary**: `verify_alignment_drift.py` checks marker-level headers
    58	for supported code/config files. Exact visual style remains a manual checklist
    59	gate.
    60	
    61	### No Commented-Out Code
    62	
    63	```markdown
    64	[ ] No commented-out code blocks present
    65	    - Use version control for code history
    66	    - Explanatory comments are OK
    67	    - TODO comments with context are OK
    68	```
